msgstr "Matériel"

#: C/config-system.xml:629(title)
msgid "Digital Cameras"
msgstr "Appareils photo numériques"

#: C/config-system.xml:630(para)
msgid ""
"Most USB digital cameras will be automatically detected by Kubuntu. Simply "
"plug in and switch on your USB digital camera, Kubuntu will then ask you if "
"you would like to import the photos from your camera. Click on "
"<guibutton>Import</guibutton>, Kubuntu will then show you a preview of your "
"photos. Choose a location to save your photos to, then click on "
"<guibutton>Import</guibutton>. Kubuntu will then save your photos to your "
"hard drive."
msgstr ""
"La plupart des appareils photo numériques USB seront détectés "
"automatiquement par Kubuntu. Connectez simplement l'appareil  USB et allumez-"
"le, Kubuntu vous demandera si vous voulez importer les photos depuis votre "
"appareil. Cliquez sur <guibutton>Importer</guibutton>, Kubuntu vous montrera "
"ensuite une prévisualisation de vos photos. Choisissez un emplacement où "
"enregistrer vos photos, cliquez sur <guibutton>Importer</guibutton>. Kubuntu "
"enregistrera ensuite vos photos sur votre disque dur."

#: C/config-system.xml:640(para)
msgid ""
"If you do not get the auto-import popup with your camera, it might be worth "
"installing <application>digiKam</application> from the "
"<emphasis>Universe</emphasis> repository (see <xref linkend=\"extra-"
